149 static constexpr char kPipelineCompilationJobZoneName[] =

152 #define RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(phase, ...) \
153  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!Run<phase>(__VA_ARGS__))) return {};
154 
155 #define PIPELINE_RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(pipeline, phase, ...) \
156  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!(pipeline).Run<phase>(__VA_ARGS__))) return {};
157 
158 class PipelineImpl final {
159  public:
160  explicit PipelineImpl(TFPipelineData* data) : data_(data) {}
161 
162  // Helpers for executing pipeline phases.
163  template <turboshaft::TurbofanPhase Phase, typename... Args>
164  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT bool Run(Args&&... args);
165 
166  // Step A.1. Initialize the heap broker.
167  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT bool InitializeHeapBroker();
168 
169  // Step A.2. Run the graph creation and initial optimization passes.
170  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT bool CreateGraph(Linkage* linkage);
171 
172  // Step B. Run the concurrent optimization passes.
173  bool OptimizeTurbofanGraph(Linkage* linkage);
174 
175  // Substep B.1. Produce a scheduled graph.
176  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT bool ComputeScheduledGraph();
177 
178 #if V8_ENABLE_WASM_SIMD256_REVEC
179  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT bool Revectorize();
180 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WASM_SIMD256_REVEC
181 
182  // Substep B.3. Run register allocation on the instruction sequence.
183  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT bool AllocateRegisters(CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
184  bool has_dummy_end_block);
185 
186  // Step C. Run the code finalization pass.
187  MaybeDirectHandle<Code> FinalizeCode(bool retire_broker = true);
188 
189  // Step D. Install any code dependencies.
190  bool CommitDependencies(Handle<Code> code);
191 
192  void RunPrintAndVerify(const char* phase, bool untyped = false);
193 
194  TFPipelineData* data() const { return data_; }
195  OptimizedCompilationInfo* info() const;
196  Isolate* isolate() const;
197  CodeGenerator* code_generator() const;
198 
199  ObserveNodeManager* observe_node_manager() const;
200 
201  private:
202  TFPipelineData* const data_;
203 };

207 class SourcePositionWrapper final : public Reducer {
208  public:
209  SourcePositionWrapper(Reducer* reducer, SourcePositionTable* table)
210  : reducer_(reducer), table_(table) {}
211  ~SourcePositionWrapper() final = default;
212  SourcePositionWrapper(const SourcePositionWrapper&) = delete;
213  SourcePositionWrapper& operator=(const SourcePositionWrapper&) = delete;
214 
215  const char* reducer_name() const override { return reducer_->reducer_name(); }
216 
217  Reduction Reduce(Node* node) final {
218  SourcePosition const pos = table_->GetSourcePosition(node);
219  SourcePositionTable::Scope position(table_, pos);
220  return reducer_->Reduce(node, nullptr);
221  }
222 
223  void Finalize() final { reducer_->Finalize(); }
224 
225  private:
226  Reducer* const reducer_;
227  SourcePositionTable* const table_;
228 };
229 
230 class NodeOriginsWrapper final : public Reducer {
231  public:
232  NodeOriginsWrapper(Reducer* reducer, NodeOriginTable* table)
233  : reducer_(reducer), table_(table) {}
234  ~NodeOriginsWrapper() final = default;
235  NodeOriginsWrapper(const NodeOriginsWrapper&) = delete;
236  NodeOriginsWrapper& operator=(const NodeOriginsWrapper&) = delete;
237 
238  const char* reducer_name() const override { return reducer_->reducer_name(); }
239 
240  Reduction Reduce(Node* node) final {
241  NodeOriginTable::Scope position(table_, reducer_name(), node);
242  return reducer_->Reduce(node, nullptr);
243  }
244 
245  void Finalize() final { reducer_->Finalize(); }
246 
247  private:
248  Reducer* const reducer_;
249  NodeOriginTable* const table_;
250 };

286 // LocalIsolateScope encapsulates the phase where persistent handles are
287 // attached to the LocalHeap inside {local_isolate}.
288 class V8_NODISCARD LocalIsolateScope {
289  public:
290  explicit LocalIsolateScope(JSHeapBroker* broker,
291  OptimizedCompilationInfo* info,
292  LocalIsolate* local_isolate)
293  : broker_(broker), info_(info) {
294  broker_->AttachLocalIsolate(info_, local_isolate);
295  info_->tick_counter().AttachLocalHeap(local_isolate->heap());
296  }
297 
298  ~LocalIsolateScope() {
299  info_->tick_counter().DetachLocalHeap();
300  broker_->DetachLocalIsolate(info_);
301  }
302 
303  private:
304  JSHeapBroker* broker_;
305  OptimizedCompilationInfo* info_;
306 };

308 void PrintFunctionSource(OptimizedCompilationInfo* info, Isolate* isolate,
309  int source_id,
310  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared) {
311  if (!IsUndefined(shared->script(), isolate)) {
312  DirectHandle<Script> script(Cast<Script>(shared->script()), isolate);
313 
314  if (!IsUndefined(script->source(), isolate)) {
315  CodeTracer::StreamScope tracing_scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
316  Tagged<Object> source_name = script->name();
317  auto& os = tracing_scope.stream();
318  os << "--- FUNCTION SOURCE (";
319  if (IsString(source_name)) {
320  os << Cast<String>(source_name)->ToCString().get() << ":";
321  }
322  os << shared->DebugNameCStr().get() << ") id{";
323  os << info->optimization_id() << "," << source_id << "} start{";
324  os << shared->StartPosition() << "} ---\n";
325  {
326  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
327  int start = shared->StartPosition();
328  int len = shared->EndPosition() - start;
329  SubStringRange source(Cast<String>(script->source()), no_gc, start,
330  len);
331  for (auto c : source) {
332  os << AsReversiblyEscapedUC16(c);
333  }
334  }
335 
336  os << "\n--- END ---\n";
337  }
338  }
339 }
340 
341 // Print information for the given inlining: which function was inlined and
342 // where the inlining occurred.
343 void PrintInlinedFunctionInfo(
344  OptimizedCompilationInfo* info, Isolate* isolate, int source_id,
345  int inlining_id, const OptimizedCompilationInfo::InlinedFunctionHolder& h) {
346  CodeTracer::StreamScope tracing_scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
347  auto& os = tracing_scope.stream();
348  os << "INLINE (" << h.shared_info->DebugNameCStr().get() << ") id{"
349  << info->optimization_id() << "," << source_id << "} AS " << inlining_id
350  << " AT ";
351  const SourcePosition position = h.position.position;
352  if (position.IsKnown()) {
353  os << "<" << position.InliningId() << ":" << position.ScriptOffset() << ">";
354  } else {
355  os << "<?>";
356  }
357  os << std::endl;
358 }
359 
360 // Print the source of all functions that participated in this optimizing
361 // compilation. For inlined functions print source position of their inlining.
362 void PrintParticipatingSource(OptimizedCompilationInfo* info,
363  Isolate* isolate) {
364  SourceIdAssigner id_assigner(info->inlined_functions().size());
365  PrintFunctionSource(info, isolate, -1, info->shared_info());
366  const auto& inlined = info->inlined_functions();
367  for (unsigned id = 0; id < inlined.size(); id++) {
368  const int source_id = id_assigner.GetIdFor(inlined[id].shared_info);
369  PrintFunctionSource(info, isolate, source_id, inlined[id].shared_info);
370  PrintInlinedFunctionInfo(info, isolate, source_id, id, inlined[id]);
371  }
372 }

374 void TraceScheduleAndVerify(OptimizedCompilationInfo* info,
375  TFPipelineData* data, Schedule* schedule,
376  const char* phase_name) {
377  RCS_SCOPE(data->runtime_call_stats(),
378  RuntimeCallCounterId::kOptimizeTraceScheduleAndVerify,
379  RuntimeCallStats::kThreadSpecific);
380  TRACE_EVENT0(TurbofanPipelineStatistics::kTraceCategory,
381  "V8.TraceScheduleAndVerify");
382 
383  TraceSchedule(info, data, schedule, phase_name);
384 
385  if (v8_flags.turbo_verify) ScheduleVerifier::Run(schedule);
386 }

388 void AddReducer(TFPipelineData* data, GraphReducer* graph_reducer,
389  Reducer* reducer) {
390  if (data->info()->source_positions()) {
391  SourcePositionWrapper* const wrapper =
392  data->graph_zone()->New<SourcePositionWrapper>(
393  reducer, data->source_positions());
394  reducer = wrapper;
395  }
396  if (data->info()->trace_turbo_json()) {
397  NodeOriginsWrapper* const wrapper =
398  data->graph_zone()->New<NodeOriginsWrapper>(reducer,
399  data->node_origins());
400  reducer = wrapper;
401  }
402 
403  graph_reducer->AddReducer(reducer);
404 }

406 TurbofanPipelineStatistics* CreatePipelineStatistics(
407  DirectHandle<Script> script, OptimizedCompilationInfo* info,
408  Isolate* isolate, ZoneStats* zone_stats) {
409  TurbofanPipelineStatistics* pipeline_statistics = nullptr;
410 
411  bool tracing_enabled;
412  TRACE_EVENT_CATEGORY_GROUP_ENABLED(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.turbofan"),
413  &tracing_enabled);
414  if (tracing_enabled || v8_flags.turbo_stats || v8_flags.turbo_stats_nvp) {
415  pipeline_statistics = new TurbofanPipelineStatistics(
416  info, isolate->GetTurboStatistics(), zone_stats);
417  pipeline_statistics->BeginPhaseKind("V8.TFInitializing");
418  }
419 
420  if (info->trace_turbo_json()) {
421  TurboJsonFile json_of(info, std::ios_base::trunc);
422  json_of << "{\"function\" : ";
423  JsonPrintFunctionSource(json_of, -1, info->GetDebugName(), script, isolate,
424  info->shared_info());
425  json_of << ",\n\"phases\":[";
426  }
427 
428  return pipeline_statistics;
429 }
430 
431 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
432 TurbofanPipelineStatistics* CreatePipelineStatistics(
433  WasmCompilationData& compilation_data, const wasm::WasmModule* wasm_module,
434  OptimizedCompilationInfo* info, ZoneStats* zone_stats) {
435  TurbofanPipelineStatistics* pipeline_statistics = nullptr;
436 
437  bool tracing_enabled;
438  TRACE_EVENT_CATEGORY_GROUP_ENABLED(
439  TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.wasm.turbofan"), &tracing_enabled);
440  if (tracing_enabled || v8_flags.turbo_stats_wasm) {
441  pipeline_statistics = new TurbofanPipelineStatistics(
442  info, wasm::GetWasmEngine()->GetOrCreateTurboStatistics(), zone_stats);
443  pipeline_statistics->BeginPhaseKind("V8.WasmInitializing");
444  }
445 
446  if (info->trace_turbo_json()) {
447  TurboJsonFile json_of(info, std::ios_base::trunc);
448  std::unique_ptr<char[]> function_name = info->GetDebugName();
449  json_of << "{\"function\":\"" << function_name.get() << "\", \"source\":\"";
450  std::ostringstream disassembly;
451  std::vector<uint32_t> source_positions;
452  base::Vector<const uint8_t> function_bytes{compilation_data.func_body.start,
453  compilation_data.body_size()};
454  base::Vector<const uint8_t> module_bytes{nullptr, 0};
455  std::optional<wasm::ModuleWireBytes> maybe_wire_bytes =
456  compilation_data.wire_bytes_storage->GetModuleBytes();
457  if (maybe_wire_bytes) module_bytes = maybe_wire_bytes->module_bytes();
458 
459  wasm::DisassembleFunction(
460  wasm_module, compilation_data.func_index, function_bytes, module_bytes,
461  compilation_data.func_body.offset, disassembly, &source_positions);
462  for (const auto& c : disassembly.str()) {
463  json_of << AsEscapedUC16ForJSON(c);
464  }
465  json_of << "\",\n\"sourceLineToBytecodePosition\" : [";
466  bool insert_comma = false;
467  for (auto val : source_positions) {
468  if (insert_comma) {
469  json_of << ", ";
470  }
471  json_of << val;
472  insert_comma = true;
473  }
474  json_of << "],\n\"phases\":[";
475  }
476 
477  return pipeline_statistics;
478 }
479 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
480 
481 // This runs instruction selection, register allocation and code generation.
482 [[nodiscard]] bool GenerateCodeFromTurboshaftGraph(
483  Linkage* linkage, turboshaft::Pipeline& turboshaft_pipeline,
484  PipelineImpl* turbofan_pipeline = nullptr,
485  std::shared_ptr<OsrHelper> osr_helper = {}) {
486  turboshaft::PipelineData* turboshaft_data = turboshaft_pipeline.data();
487  turboshaft_data->InitializeCodegenComponent(osr_helper);
488  // Run Turboshaft instruction selection.
489  if (!turboshaft_pipeline.PrepareForInstructionSelection()) return false;
490  if (!turboshaft_pipeline.SelectInstructions(linkage)) return false;
491  // We can release the graph now.
492  turboshaft_data->ClearGraphComponent();
493 
494  if (!turboshaft_pipeline.AllocateRegisters(
495  linkage->GetIncomingDescriptor())) {
496  return false;
497  }
498  if (!turboshaft_pipeline.AssembleCode(linkage)) {
499  return false;
500  }
501  return true;
502 }

506 class PipelineCompilationJob final : public TurbofanCompilationJob {
507  public:
508  PipelineCompilationJob(Isolate* isolate,
509  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info,
510  Handle<JSFunction> function, BytecodeOffset osr_offset,
511  CodeKind code_kind);
512  ~PipelineCompilationJob() final;
513  PipelineCompilationJob(const PipelineCompilationJob&) = delete;
514  PipelineCompilationJob& operator=(const PipelineCompilationJob&) = delete;
515 
516  protected:
517  Status PrepareJobImpl(Isolate* isolate) final;
518  Status ExecuteJobImpl(RuntimeCallStats* stats,
519  LocalIsolate* local_isolate) final;
520  Status FinalizeJobImpl(Isolate* isolate) final;
521 
522  private:
523  Zone zone_;
524  ZoneStats zone_stats_;
525  OptimizedCompilationInfo compilation_info_;
526  std::unique_ptr<TurbofanPipelineStatistics> pipeline_statistics_;
527  TFPipelineData data_;
528  turboshaft::PipelineData turboshaft_data_;
529  PipelineImpl pipeline_;
530  Linkage* linkage_;
531 };
532 
533 PipelineCompilationJob::PipelineCompilationJob(
534  Isolate* isolate, Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info,
535  Handle<JSFunction> function, BytecodeOffset osr_offset, CodeKind code_kind)
536  // Note that the OptimizedCompilationInfo is not initialized at the time
537  // we pass it to the CompilationJob constructor, but it is not
538  // dereferenced there.
539  : TurbofanCompilationJob(isolate, &compilation_info_,
540  CompilationJob::State::kReadyToPrepare),
541  zone_(isolate->allocator(), kPipelineCompilationJobZoneName),
542  zone_stats_(isolate->allocator()),
543  compilation_info_(&zone_, isolate, shared_info, function, code_kind,
544  osr_offset),
545  pipeline_statistics_(CreatePipelineStatistics(
546  direct_handle(Cast<Script>(shared_info->script()), isolate),
547  compilation_info(), isolate, &zone_stats_)),
548  data_(&zone_stats_, isolate, compilation_info(),
549  pipeline_statistics_.get()),
550  turboshaft_data_(&zone_stats_, turboshaft::TurboshaftPipelineKind::kJS,
551  isolate, compilation_info(),
552  AssemblerOptions::Default(isolate)),
553  pipeline_(&data_),
554  linkage_(nullptr) {
555  turboshaft_data_.set_pipeline_statistics(pipeline_statistics_.get());
556 }
557 
558 PipelineCompilationJob::~PipelineCompilationJob() = default;

560 void TraceSchedule(OptimizedCompilationInfo* info, TFPipelineData* data,
561  Schedule* schedule, const char* phase_name) {
562  if (info->trace_turbo_json()) {
563  UnparkedScopeIfNeeded scope(data->broker());
564  AllowHandleDereference allow_deref;
565 
566  TurboJsonFile json_of(info, std::ios_base::app);
567  json_of << "{\"name\":\"" << phase_name << "\",\"type\":\"schedule\""
568  << ",\"data\":\"";
569  std::stringstream schedule_stream;
570  schedule_stream << *schedule;
571  std::string schedule_string(schedule_stream.str());
572  for (const auto& c : schedule_string) {
573  json_of << AsEscapedUC16ForJSON(c);
574  }
575  json_of << "\"},\n";
576  }
577 
578  if (info->trace_turbo_graph() || v8_flags.trace_turbo_scheduler) {
579  UnparkedScopeIfNeeded scope(data->broker());
580  AllowHandleDereference allow_deref;
581 
582  CodeTracer::StreamScope tracing_scope(data->GetCodeTracer());
583  tracing_scope.stream() << "----- " << phase_name << " -----\n" << *schedule;
584  }
585 }
586 
587 // Print the code after compiling it.
588 void PrintCode(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Code> code,
589  OptimizedCompilationInfo* info) {
590  if (v8_flags.print_opt_source && info->IsOptimizing()) {
591  PrintParticipatingSource(info, isolate);
592  }
593 
594 #ifdef ENABLE_DISASSEMBLER
595  const bool print_code =
596  v8_flags.print_code ||
597  (info->IsOptimizing() && v8_flags.print_opt_code &&
598  info->shared_info()->PassesFilter(v8_flags.print_opt_code_filter));
599  if (print_code) {
600  std::unique_ptr<char[]> debug_name = info->GetDebugName();
601  CodeTracer::StreamScope tracing_scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
602  std::ostream& os = tracing_scope.stream();
603 
604  // Print the source code if available.
605  const bool print_source = info->IsOptimizing();
606  if (print_source) {
607  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = info->shared_info();
608  if (IsScript(shared->script()) &&
609  !IsUndefined(Cast<Script>(shared->script())->source(), isolate)) {
610  os << "--- Raw source ---\n";
611  StringCharacterStream stream(
612  Cast<String>(Cast<Script>(shared->script())->source()),
613  shared->StartPosition());
614  // fun->end_position() points to the last character in the stream. We
615  // need to compensate by adding one to calculate the length.
616  int source_len = shared->EndPosition() - shared->StartPosition() + 1;
617  for (int i = 0; i < source_len; i++) {
618  if (stream.HasMore()) {
619  os << AsReversiblyEscapedUC16(stream.GetNext());
620  }
621  }
622  os << "\n\n";
623  }
624  }
625  if (info->IsOptimizing()) {
626  os << "--- Optimized code ---\n"
627  << "optimization_id = " << info->optimization_id() << "\n";
628  } else {
629  os << "--- Code ---\n";
630  }
631  if (print_source) {
632  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = info->shared_info();
633  os << "source_position = " << shared->StartPosition() << "\n";
634  }
635  code->Disassemble(debug_name.get(), os, isolate);
636  os << "--- End code ---\n";
637  }
638 #endif // ENABLE_DISASSEMBLER
639 }
640 
641 // The CheckMaps node can migrate objects with deprecated maps. Afterwards, we
642 // check the resulting object against a fixed list of maps known at compile
643 // time. This is problematic if we made any assumptions about an object with the
644 // deprecated map, as it now changed shape. Therefore, we want to avoid
645 // embedding deprecated maps, as objects with these maps can be changed by
646 // CheckMaps.
647 // The following code only checks for deprecated maps at the end of compilation,
648 // but doesn't protect us against the embedded maps becoming deprecated later.
649 // However, this is enough, since if the map becomes deprecated later, it will
650 // migrate to a new map not yet known at compile time, so if we migrate to it as
651 // part of a CheckMaps, this check will always fail afterwards and deoptimize.
652 // This in turn relies on a runtime invariant that map migrations always target
653 // newly allocated maps.
654 bool CheckNoDeprecatedMaps(DirectHandle<Code> code, Isolate* isolate) {
655  int mode_mask = RelocInfo::EmbeddedObjectModeMask();
656  for (RelocIterator it(*code, mode_mask); !it.done(); it.next()) {
657  DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsEmbeddedObjectMode(it.rinfo()->rmode()));
658  Tagged<HeapObject> obj = it.rinfo()->target_object(isolate);
659  if (IsMap(obj) && Cast<Map>(obj)->is_deprecated()) {
660  return false;
661  }
662  }
663  return true;
664 }
665 
666 namespace {
667 // Ensure that the RuntimeStats table is set on the PipelineData for
668 // duration of the job phase and unset immediately afterwards. Each job
669 // needs to set the correct RuntimeCallStats table depending on whether it
670 // is running on a background or foreground thread.
671 class V8_NODISCARD PipelineJobScope {
672  public:
673  PipelineJobScope(TFPipelineData* data, RuntimeCallStats* stats)
674  : data_(data), current_broker_(data_->broker()) {
675  data_->set_runtime_call_stats(stats);
676  }
677  PipelineJobScope(turboshaft::PipelineData* turboshaft_data,
678  RuntimeCallStats* stats)
679  : turboshaft_data_(turboshaft_data),
680  current_broker_(turboshaft_data_->broker()) {
681  turboshaft_data_->set_runtime_call_stats(stats);
682  }
683 
684  ~PipelineJobScope() {
685  if (data_) data_->set_runtime_call_stats(nullptr);
686  if (turboshaft_data_) turboshaft_data_->set_runtime_call_stats(nullptr);
687  }
688 
689  private:
690  HighAllocationThroughputScope high_throughput_scope_{
691  V8::GetCurrentPlatform()};
692  TFPipelineData* data_ = nullptr;
693  turboshaft::PipelineData* turboshaft_data_ = nullptr;
694  CurrentHeapBrokerScope current_broker_;
695 };
696 } // namespace
697 
698 PipelineCompilationJob::Status PipelineCompilationJob::PrepareJobImpl(
699  Isolate* isolate) {
700  // Ensure that the RuntimeCallStats table of main thread is available for
701  // phases happening during PrepareJob.
702  PipelineJobScope scope(&data_, isolate->counters()->runtime_call_stats());
703 
704  if (compilation_info()->bytecode_array()->length() >
705  v8_flags.max_optimized_bytecode_size) {
706  return AbortOptimization(BailoutReason::kFunctionTooBig);
707  }
708 
709  if (!v8_flags.always_turbofan) {
710  compilation_info()->set_bailout_on_uninitialized();
711  }
712  if (v8_flags.turbo_loop_peeling) {
713  compilation_info()->set_loop_peeling();
714  }
715  if (v8_flags.turbo_inlining) {
716  compilation_info()->set_inlining();
717  }
718  if (v8_flags.turbo_allocation_folding) {
719  compilation_info()->set_allocation_folding();
720  }
721 
722  // Determine whether to specialize the code for the function's context.
723  // We can't do this in the case of OSR, because we want to cache the
724  // generated code on the native context keyed on SharedFunctionInfo.
725  // TODO(mythria): Check if it is better to key the OSR cache on JSFunction and
726  // allow context specialization for OSR code.
727  if (!compilation_info()
728  ->shared_info()
729  ->function_context_independent_compiled() &&
730  compilation_info()->closure()->raw_feedback_cell()->map() ==
731  ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).one_closure_cell_map() &&
732  !compilation_info()->is_osr()) {
733  compilation_info()->set_function_context_specializing();
734  data_.ChooseSpecializationContext();
735  }
736 
737  if (compilation_info()->source_positions()) {
738  SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(
739  isolate, compilation_info()->shared_info());
740  }
741 
742  data_.set_start_source_position(
743  compilation_info()->shared_info()->StartPosition());
744 
745  linkage_ = compilation_info()->zone()->New<Linkage>(
746  Linkage::ComputeIncoming(compilation_info()->zone(), compilation_info()));
747 
748  if (compilation_info()->is_osr()) data_.InitializeOsrHelper();
749 
750  // InitializeHeapBroker() and CreateGraph() may already use
751  // IsPendingAllocation.
752  isolate->heap()->PublishMainThreadPendingAllocations();
753 
754  if (!pipeline_.InitializeHeapBroker()) {
755  return FAILED;
756  }
757 
758  // Serialization may have allocated.
759  isolate->heap()->PublishMainThreadPendingAllocations();
760 
761  return SUCCEEDED;
762 }
763 
764 PipelineCompilationJob::Status PipelineCompilationJob::ExecuteJobImpl(
765  RuntimeCallStats* stats, LocalIsolate* local_isolate) {
766  // Ensure that the RuntimeCallStats table is only available during execution
767  // and not during finalization as that might be on a different thread.
768  PipelineJobScope scope(&data_, stats);
769  LocalIsolateScope local_isolate_scope(data_.broker(), data_.info(),
770  local_isolate);
771 
772  turboshaft_data_.InitializeBrokerAndDependencies(data_.broker_ptr(),
773  data_.dependencies());
774  turboshaft::Pipeline turboshaft_pipeline(&turboshaft_data_);
775  if (compilation_info_.was_cancelled()) {
776  return AbortOptimization(BailoutReason::kCancelled);
777  }
778 
779  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.turbolev)) {
780  if (!turboshaft_pipeline.CreateGraphWithMaglev(linkage_)) {
781  return AbortOptimization(BailoutReason::kTurbofanGraphBuildingFailed);
782  }
783  } else {
784  if (!pipeline_.CreateGraph(linkage_)) {
785  return AbortOptimization(BailoutReason::kTurbofanGraphBuildingFailed);
786  }
787 
788  // We selectively Unpark inside OptimizeTurbofanGraph.
789  if (!pipeline_.OptimizeTurbofanGraph(linkage_)) return FAILED;
790 
791  // We convert the turbofan graph to turboshaft.
792  if (!turboshaft_pipeline.CreateGraphFromTurbofan(&data_, linkage_)) {
793  data_.EndPhaseKind();
794  return FAILED;
795  }
796  }
797 
798  if (!turboshaft_pipeline.OptimizeTurboshaftGraph(linkage_)) {
799  return FAILED;
800  }
801 
802  const bool success = GenerateCodeFromTurboshaftGraph(
803  linkage_, turboshaft_pipeline, &pipeline_, data_.osr_helper_ptr());
804  return success ? SUCCEEDED : FAILED;
805 }
806 
807 PipelineCompilationJob::Status PipelineCompilationJob::FinalizeJobImpl(
808  Isolate* isolate) {
809  // Ensure that the RuntimeCallStats table of main thread is available for
810  // phases happening during PrepareJob.
811  PipelineJobScope scope(&data_, isolate->counters()->runtime_call_stats());
812  RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kOptimizeFinalizePipelineJob);
813  Handle<Code> code;
814  DirectHandle<NativeContext> context;
815  turboshaft::Pipeline turboshaft_pipeline(&turboshaft_data_);
816  MaybeHandle<Code> maybe_code = turboshaft_pipeline.FinalizeCode();
817  if (!maybe_code.ToHandle(&code)) {
818  if (compilation_info()->bailout_reason() == BailoutReason::kNoReason) {
819  return AbortOptimization(BailoutReason::kTurbofanCodeGenerationFailed);
820  }
821  return FAILED;
822  }
823  context = DirectHandle<NativeContext>(compilation_info()->native_context(),
824  isolate);
825  if (context->IsDetached(isolate)) {
826  return AbortOptimization(BailoutReason::kDetachedNativeContext);
827  }
828  if (!CheckNoDeprecatedMaps(code, isolate)) {
829  return RetryOptimization(BailoutReason::kConcurrentMapDeprecation);
830  }
831  if (!turboshaft_pipeline.CommitDependencies(code)) {
832  return RetryOptimization(BailoutReason::kBailedOutDueToDependencyChange);
833  }
834  compilation_info()->SetCode(code);
835  GlobalHandleVector<Map> maps = CollectRetainedMaps(isolate, code);
836  RegisterWeakObjectsInOptimizedCode(isolate, context, code, std::move(maps));
837  return SUCCEEDED;
838 }
839 
840 template <turboshaft::TurbofanPhase Phase, typename... Args>
841 bool PipelineImpl::Run(Args&&... args) {
842 #ifdef V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
843  PipelineRunScope scope(this->data_, Phase::phase_name(),
844  Phase::kRuntimeCallCounterId, Phase::kCounterMode);
845 #else
846  PipelineRunScope scope(this->data_, Phase::phase_name());
847 #endif
848  Phase phase;
849  static_assert(Phase::kKind == PhaseKind::kTurbofan);
850  phase.Run(this->data_, scope.zone(), std::forward<Args>(args)...);
851  return !info()->was_cancelled();
852 }

854 struct GraphBuilderPhase {
855  DECL_PIPELINE_PHASE_CONSTANTS(BytecodeGraphBuilder)
856 
857  void Run(TFPipelineData* data, Zone* temp_zone, Linkage* linkage) {
858  BytecodeGraphBuilderFlags flags;
859  if (data->info()->analyze_environment_liveness()) {
860  flags |= BytecodeGraphBuilderFlag::kAnalyzeEnvironmentLiveness;
861  }
862  if (data->info()->bailout_on_uninitialized()) {
863  flags |= BytecodeGraphBuilderFlag::kBailoutOnUninitialized;
864  }
865 
866  JSHeapBroker* broker = data->broker();
867  UnparkedScopeIfNeeded scope(broker);
868  SharedFunctionInfoRef sfi_ref =
869  MakeRef(broker, data->info()->closure()->shared());
870  FeedbackCellRef feedback_cell_ref =
871  MakeRef(broker, data->info()->closure()->raw_feedback_cell());
872  BytecodeArrayRef bytecode = MakeRef(broker, data->info()->bytecode_array());
873  CallFrequency frequency(1.0f);
874  BuildGraphFromBytecode(broker, temp_zone, sfi_ref, bytecode,
875  feedback_cell_ref, data->info()->osr_offset(),
876  data->jsgraph(), frequency, data->source_positions(),
877  data->node_origins(), SourcePosition::kNotInlined,
878  data->info()->code_kind(), flags,
879  &data->info()->tick_counter(),
880  ObserveNodeInfo{data->observe_node_manager(),
881  data->info()->node_observer()});
882 
883  // We need to be certain that the parameter count reported by our output
884  // Code object matches what the code we compile expects. Otherwise, this
885  // may lead to effectively signature mismatches during function calls. This
886  // CHECK is a defense-in-depth measure to ensure this doesn't happen.
887  SBXCHECK_EQ(
888  StartNode(data->jsgraph()->graph()->start()).FormalParameterCount(),
889  linkage->GetIncomingDescriptor()->ParameterSlotCount());
890  }
891 };
892 
893 struct InliningPhase {
894  DECL_PIPELINE_PHASE_CONSTANTS(Inlining)
895 
896  void Run(TFPipelineData* data, Zone* temp_zone) {
897  OptimizedCompilationInfo* info = data->info();
898  GraphReducer graph_reducer(temp_zone, data->graph(), &info->tick_counter(),
899  data->broker(), data->jsgraph()->Dead(),
900  data->observe_node_manager());
901  DeadCodeElimination dead_code_elimination(&graph_reducer, data->graph(),
902  data->common(), temp_zone);
903  CheckpointElimination checkpoint_elimination(&graph_reducer);
904  CommonOperatorReducer common_reducer(
905  &graph_reducer, data->graph(), data->broker(), data->common(),
906  data->machine(), temp_zone, BranchSemantics::kJS);
907  JSCallReducer::Flags call_reducer_flags = JSCallReducer::kNoFlags;
908  if (data->info()->bailout_on_uninitialized()) {
909  call_reducer_flags |= JSCallReducer::kBailoutOnUninitialized;
910  }
911  if (data->info()->inline_js_wasm_calls() && data->info()->inlining()) {
912  call_reducer_flags |= JSCallReducer::kInlineJSToWasmCalls;
913  }
914  JSCallReducer call_reducer(&graph_reducer, data->jsgraph(), data->broker(),
915  temp_zone, call_reducer_flags);
916  JSContextSpecialization context_specialization(
917  &graph_reducer, data->jsgraph(), data->broker(),
918  data->specialization_context(),
919  data->info()->function_context_specializing()
920  ? data->info()->closure()
921  : MaybeHandle<JSFunction>());
922  JSNativeContextSpecialization::Flags flags =
923  JSNativeContextSpecialization::kNoFlags;
924  if (data->info()->bailout_on_uninitialized()) {
925  flags |= JSNativeContextSpecialization::kBailoutOnUninitialized;
926  }
927  // Passing the OptimizedCompilationInfo's shared zone here as
928  // JSNativeContextSpecialization allocates out-of-heap objects
929  // that need to live until code generation.
930  JSNativeContextSpecialization native_context_specialization(
931  &graph_reducer, data->jsgraph(), data->broker(), flags, temp_zone,
932  info->zone());
933  JSInliningHeuristic inlining(
934  &graph_reducer, temp_zone, data->info(), data->jsgraph(),
935  data->broker(), data->source_positions(), data->node_origins(),
936  JSInliningHeuristic::kJSOnly, nullptr, nullptr);
937 
938  JSIntrinsicLowering intrinsic_lowering(&graph_reducer, data->jsgraph(),
939  data->broker());
940  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &dead_code_elimination);
941  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &checkpoint_elimination);
942  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &common_reducer);
943  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &native_context_specialization);
944  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &context_specialization);
945  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &intrinsic_lowering);
946  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &call_reducer);
947  if (data->info()->inlining()) {
948  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &inlining);
949  }
950  graph_reducer.ReduceGraph();
951  info->set_inlined_bytecode_size(inlining.total_inlined_bytecode_size());
952 
953 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
954  // Not forwarding this information to the TurboFan pipeline data here later
955  // skips `JSWasmInliningPhase` if there are no JS-to-Wasm functions calls.
956  if (call_reducer.has_js_wasm_calls()) {
957  const wasm::WasmModule* wasm_module =
958  call_reducer.wasm_module_for_inlining();
959  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(wasm_module);
960  data->set_wasm_module_for_inlining(wasm_module);
961  // Enable source positions if not enabled yet. While JS only uses the
962  // source position table for tracing, profiling, ..., wasm needs it at
963  // compile time for keeping track of source locations for wasm traps.
964  // Note: By not setting data->info()->set_source_positions(), even with
965  // wasm inlining, source positions shouldn't be kept alive after
966  // compilation is finished (if not for tracing, ...)
967  if (!data->source_positions()->IsEnabled()) {
968  data->source_positions()->Enable();
969  data->source_positions()->AddDecorator();
970  }
971  }
972 #endif
973  }
974 };
975 
976 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
977 struct JSWasmInliningPhase {
978  DECL_PIPELINE_PHASE_CONSTANTS(JSWasmInlining)
979  void Run(TFPipelineData* data, Zone* temp_zone) {
980  DCHECK(data->has_js_wasm_calls());
981  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(data->wasm_module_for_inlining());
982 
983  OptimizedCompilationInfo* info = data->info();
984  GraphReducer graph_reducer(temp_zone, data->graph(), &info->tick_counter(),
985  data->broker(), data->jsgraph()->Dead());
986  DeadCodeElimination dead_code_elimination(&graph_reducer, data->graph(),
987  data->common(), temp_zone);
988  CommonOperatorReducer common_reducer(
989  &graph_reducer, data->graph(), data->broker(), data->common(),
990  data->machine(), temp_zone, BranchSemantics::kMachine);
991  // If we want to inline in Turboshaft instead (i.e., later in the
992  // pipeline), only inline the wrapper here in TurboFan.
993  // TODO(dlehmann,353475584): Long-term, also inline the JS-to-Wasm wrappers
994  // in Turboshaft (or in Maglev, depending on the shared frontend).
995  JSInliningHeuristic::Mode mode =
996  (v8_flags.turboshaft_wasm_in_js_inlining)
997  ? JSInliningHeuristic::kWasmWrappersOnly
998  : JSInliningHeuristic::kWasmFullInlining;
999  JSInliningHeuristic inlining(
1000  &graph_reducer, temp_zone, data->info(), data->jsgraph(),
1001  data->broker(), data->source_positions(), data->node_origins(), mode,
1002  data->wasm_module_for_inlining(), data->js_wasm_calls_sidetable());
1003  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &dead_code_elimination);
1004  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &common_reducer);
1005  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &inlining);
1006  graph_reducer.ReduceGraph();
1007  }
1008 };

1010 struct JSWasmLoweringPhase {

1012  void Run(TFPipelineData* data, Zone* temp_zone) {
1013  DCHECK(data->has_js_wasm_calls());
1014  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(data->wasm_module_for_inlining());

1030 struct EarlyGraphTrimmingPhase {
1031  DECL_PIPELINE_PHASE_CONSTANTS(EarlyGraphTrimming)
1032 
1033  void Run(TFPipelineData* data, Zone* temp_zone) {
1034  GraphTrimmer trimmer(temp_zone, data->graph());
1035  NodeVector roots(temp_zone);
1036  data->jsgraph()->GetCachedNodes(&roots);
1037  UnparkedScopeIfNeeded scope(data->broker(), v8_flags.trace_turbo_trimming);
1038  trimmer.TrimGraph(roots.begin(), roots.end());

1042 struct TyperPhase {
1043  DECL_PIPELINE_PHASE_CONSTANTS(Typer)
1044 
1045  void Run(TFPipelineData* data, Zone* temp_zone, Typer* typer) {
1046  NodeVector roots(temp_zone);
1047  data->jsgraph()->GetCachedNodes(&roots);
1048 
1049  // Make sure we always type True and False. Needed for escape analysis.
1050  roots.push_back(data->jsgraph()->TrueConstant());
1051  roots.push_back(data->jsgraph()->FalseConstant());
1052 
1053  LoopVariableOptimizer induction_vars(data->jsgraph()->graph(),
1054  data->common(), temp_zone);
1055  if (v8_flags.turbo_loop_variable) induction_vars.Run();
1056 
1057  // The typer inspects heap objects, so we need to unpark the local heap.
1058  UnparkedScopeIfNeeded scope(data->broker());
1059  typer->Run(roots, &induction_vars);
1060  }
1061 };

1063 struct UntyperPhase {
1064  DECL_PIPELINE_PHASE_CONSTANTS(Untyper)
1065 
1066  void Run(TFPipelineData* data, Zone* temp_zone) {
1067  class RemoveTypeReducer final : public Reducer {
1068  public:
1069  const char* reducer_name() const override { return "RemoveTypeReducer"; }
1070  Reduction Reduce(Node* node) final {
1071  if (NodeProperties::IsTyped(node)) {
1072  NodeProperties::RemoveType(node);
1073  return Changed(node);
1074  }
1075  return NoChange();
1076  }
1077  };
1078 
1079  NodeVector roots(temp_zone);
1080  data->jsgraph()->GetCachedNodes(&roots);
1081  for (Node* node : roots) {
1082  NodeProperties::RemoveType(node);
1083  }
1084 
1085  GraphReducer graph_reducer(
1086  temp_zone, data->graph(), &data->info()->tick_counter(), data->broker(),
1087  data->jsgraph()->Dead(), data->observe_node_manager());
1088  RemoveTypeReducer remove_type_reducer;
1089  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &remove_type_reducer);
1090  graph_reducer.ReduceGraph();
1091  }

1335  v8_flags.trace_turbo_trimming);

1346  data->broker(), data->jsgraph(), temp_zone,

1348  ? MemoryLowering::AllocationFolding::kDoAllocationFolding
1349  : MemoryLowering::AllocationFolding::kDontAllocationFolding,
1350  data->debug_name(), &data->info()->tick_counter(), is_wasm);

1352  }

1422 struct WasmOptimizationPhase {
1423  DECL_PIPELINE_PHASE_CONSTANTS(WasmOptimization)
1424 
1425  void Run(TFPipelineData* data, Zone* temp_zone,
1426  MachineOperatorReducer::SignallingNanPropagation
1427  signalling_nan_propagation,
1428  wasm::WasmDetectedFeatures detected_features) {
1429  // Run optimizations in two rounds: First one around load elimination and
1430  // then one around branch elimination. This is because those two
1431  // optimizations sometimes display quadratic complexity when run together.
1432  // We only need load elimination for managed objects.
1433  if (detected_features.has_gc()) {
1434  GraphReducer graph_reducer(temp_zone, data->graph(),
1435  &data->info()->tick_counter(), data->broker(),
1436  data->jsgraph()->Dead(),
1437  data->observe_node_manager());
1438  MachineOperatorReducer machine_reducer(&graph_reducer, data->jsgraph(),
1439  signalling_nan_propagation);
1440  DeadCodeElimination dead_code_elimination(&graph_reducer, data->graph(),
1441  data->common(), temp_zone);
1442  CommonOperatorReducer common_reducer(
1443  &graph_reducer, data->graph(), data->broker(), data->common(),
1444  data->machine(), temp_zone, BranchSemantics::kMachine);
1445  ValueNumberingReducer value_numbering(temp_zone, data->graph()->zone());
1446  CsaLoadElimination load_elimination(&graph_reducer, data->jsgraph(),
1447  temp_zone);
1448  WasmEscapeAnalysis escape(&graph_reducer, data->mcgraph());
1449  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &machine_reducer);
1450  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &dead_code_elimination);
1451  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &common_reducer);
1452  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &value_numbering);
1453  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &load_elimination);
1454  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &escape);
1455  graph_reducer.ReduceGraph();
1456  }
1457  {
1458  GraphReducer graph_reducer(temp_zone, data->graph(),
1459  &data->info()->tick_counter(), data->broker(),
1460  data->jsgraph()->Dead(),
1461  data->observe_node_manager());
1462  MachineOperatorReducer machine_reducer(&graph_reducer, data->jsgraph(),
1463  signalling_nan_propagation);
1464  DeadCodeElimination dead_code_elimination(&graph_reducer, data->graph(),
1465  data->common(), temp_zone);
1466  CommonOperatorReducer common_reducer(
1467  &graph_reducer, data->graph(), data->broker(), data->common(),
1468  data->machine(), temp_zone, BranchSemantics::kMachine);
1469  ValueNumberingReducer value_numbering(temp_zone, data->graph()->zone());
1470  BranchElimination branch_condition_elimination(
1471  &graph_reducer, data->jsgraph(), temp_zone);
1472  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &machine_reducer);
1473  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &dead_code_elimination);
1474  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &common_reducer);
1475  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &value_numbering);
1476  AddReducer(data, &graph_reducer, &branch_condition_elimination);
1477  graph_reducer.ReduceGraph();
1478  }
1479  }
1480 };

1508 struct PrintGraphPhase {
1509  DECL_PIPELINE_PHASE_CONSTANTS(PrintGraph)
1510 
1511  void Run(TFPipelineData* data, Zone* temp_zone, const char* phase) {
1512  OptimizedCompilationInfo* info = data->info();
1513  TFGraph* graph = data->graph();
1514  if (info->trace_turbo_json()) { // Print JSON.
1515  UnparkedScopeIfNeeded scope(data->broker());
1516  AllowHandleDereference allow_deref;
1517 
1518  TurboJsonFile json_of(info, std::ios_base::app);
1519  json_of << "{\"name\":\"" << phase << "\",\"type\":\"graph\",\"data\":"
1520  << AsJSON(*graph, data->source_positions(), data->node_origins())
1521  << "},\n";
1522  }
1523 
1524  if (info->trace_turbo_scheduled()) {
1525  AccountingAllocator allocator;
1526  Schedule* schedule = data->schedule();
1527  if (schedule == nullptr) {
1528  schedule = Scheduler::ComputeSchedule(
1529  temp_zone, data->graph(), Scheduler::kNoFlags,
1530  &info->tick_counter(), data->profile_data());
1531  }
1532 
1533  UnparkedScopeIfNeeded scope(data->broker());
1534  AllowHandleDereference allow_deref;
1535  CodeTracer::StreamScope tracing_scope(data->GetCodeTracer());
1536  tracing_scope.stream()
1537  << "----- Graph after " << phase << " ----- " << std::endl
1538  << AsScheduledGraph(schedule);
1539  } else if (info->trace_turbo_graph()) { // Simple textual RPO.
1540  UnparkedScopeIfNeeded scope(data->broker());
1541  AllowHandleDereference allow_deref;
1542  CodeTracer::StreamScope tracing_scope(data->GetCodeTracer());
1543  tracing_scope.stream()
1544  << "----- Graph after " << phase << " ----- " << std::endl
1545  << AsRPO(*graph);
1546  }
1547  }
1548 };

1550 struct VerifyGraphPhase {
1551  DECL_PIPELINE_PHASE_CONSTANTS(VerifyGraph)
1552 
1553  void Run(TFPipelineData* data, Zone* temp_zone, const bool untyped,
1554  bool values_only = false) {
1555  Verifier::CodeType code_type;
1556  switch (data->info()->code_kind()) {
1557  case CodeKind::WASM_FUNCTION:
1558  case CodeKind::WASM_TO_CAPI_FUNCTION:
1559  case CodeKind::WASM_TO_JS_FUNCTION:
1560  case CodeKind::JS_TO_WASM_FUNCTION:
1561  case CodeKind::C_WASM_ENTRY:
1562  code_type = Verifier::kWasm;
1563  break;
1564  default:
1565  code_type = Verifier::kDefault;
1566  }
1567  Verifier::Run(data->graph(), !untyped ? Verifier::TYPED : Verifier::UNTYPED,
1568  values_only ? Verifier::kValuesOnly : Verifier::kAll,
1569  code_type);
1570  }
1571 };

1726 // Temporary helpers for logic shared by the TurboFan and Turboshaft wrapper
1727 // compilation jobs. Remove them once wrappers are fully ported to Turboshaft.
1728 void TraceWrapperCompilation(const char* compiler,
1729  OptimizedCompilationInfo* info,
1730  TFPipelineData* data) {
1731  if (info->trace_turbo_json() || info->trace_turbo_graph()) {
1732  CodeTracer::StreamScope tracing_scope(data->GetCodeTracer());
1733  tracing_scope.stream()
1734  << "---------------------------------------------------\n"
1735  << "Begin compiling method " << info->GetDebugName().get() << " using "
1736  << compiler << std::endl;
1737  }
1738 
1739  if (info->trace_turbo_json()) {
1740  TurboJsonFile json_of(info, std::ios_base::trunc);
1741  json_of << "{\"function\":\"" << info->GetDebugName().get()
1742  << "\", \"source\":\"\",\n\"phases\":[";
1743  }
1744 }

1747  turboshaft::PipelineData* data) {
1748  if (info->trace_turbo_json() || info->trace_turbo_graph()) {
1749  CodeTracer::StreamScope tracing_scope(data->GetCodeTracer());
1750  tracing_scope.stream()
1751  << "---------------------------------------------------\n"
1752  << "Begin compiling method " << info->GetDebugName().get()
1753  << " using Turboshaft" << std::endl;
1754  }
1755 
1756  if (info->trace_turbo_json()) {
1757  TurboJsonFile json_of(info, std::ios_base::trunc);

1759  << "\", \"source\":\"\",\n\"phases\":[";

1762 
1763 CompilationJob::Status FinalizeWrapperCompilation(
1764  turboshaft::PipelineData* turboshaft_data, OptimizedCompilationInfo* info,
1765  CallDescriptor* call_descriptor, Isolate* isolate,
1766  const char* method_name) {
1767  Handle<Code> code;
1768  turboshaft::Pipeline pipeline(turboshaft_data);
1769  if (!pipeline.FinalizeCode(call_descriptor).ToHandle(&code)) {
1770  V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(isolate, method_name);
1771  }
1772  DCHECK_NULL(turboshaft_data->depedencies());
1773  info->SetCode(code);
1774 #ifdef ENABLE_DISASSEMBLER
1775  if (v8_flags.print_wasm_code) {
1776  CodeTracer::StreamScope tracing_scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
1777  code->Disassemble(info->GetDebugName().get(), tracing_scope.stream(),
1778  isolate);
1779  }
1780 #endif
1781 
1782  if (isolate->IsLoggingCodeCreation()) {
1783  PROFILE(isolate, CodeCreateEvent(LogEventListener::CodeTag::kStub,
1784  Cast<AbstractCode>(code),
1785  info->GetDebugName().get()));
1786  }
1787  if (code->kind() == CodeKind::WASM_TO_JS_FUNCTION) {
1788  code->set_wasm_js_tagged_parameter_count(
1789  call_descriptor->GetTaggedParameterSlots() & 0xffff);
1790  code->set_wasm_js_first_tagged_parameter(
1791  call_descriptor->GetTaggedParameterSlots() >> 16);
1792  }
1793  return CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED;
1794 }
1795 } // namespace
1796 
1797 CompilationJob::Status WasmHeapStubCompilationJob::ExecuteJobImpl(
1798  RuntimeCallStats* stats, LocalIsolate* local_isolate) {
1799  std::unique_ptr<TurbofanPipelineStatistics> pipeline_statistics;
1800  if (v8_flags.turbo_stats || v8_flags.turbo_stats_nvp) {
1801  pipeline_statistics.reset(new TurbofanPipelineStatistics(
1802  &info_, wasm::GetWasmEngine()->GetOrCreateTurboStatistics(),
1803  &zone_stats_));
1804  pipeline_statistics->BeginPhaseKind("V8.WasmStubCodegen");
1805  }
1806  TraceWrapperCompilation("Turbofan", &info_, &data_);
1807  pipeline_.RunPrintAndVerify("V8.WasmMachineCode", true);
1808  if (!pipeline_.Run<MemoryOptimizationPhase>()) return FAILED;
1809  if (!pipeline_.ComputeScheduledGraph()) return FAILED;
1810 
1811  turboshaft::Pipeline turboshaft_pipeline(&turboshaft_data_);
1812 
1813  // We convert the turbofan graph to turboshaft.
1814  Linkage linkage(call_descriptor_);
1815  if (!turboshaft_pipeline.CreateGraphFromTurbofan(&data_, &linkage)) {
1816  return FAILED;
1817  }
1818 
1819  // We need to run simplification to normalize some patterns for instruction
1820  // selection (e.g. loads and stores).
1821  if (!turboshaft_pipeline.RunSimplificationAndNormalizationPhase()) {
1822  return FAILED;
1823  }
1824 
1825  const bool success = GenerateCodeFromTurboshaftGraph(
1826  &linkage, turboshaft_pipeline, &pipeline_, data_.osr_helper_ptr());
1827  return success ? SUCCEEDED : FAILED;
1828 }
1829 
1830 CompilationJob::Status WasmHeapStubCompilationJob::FinalizeJobImpl(
1831  Isolate* isolate) {
1832  return FinalizeWrapperCompilation(
1833  &turboshaft_data_, &info_, call_descriptor_, isolate,
1834  "WasmHeapStubCompilationJob::FinalizeJobImpl");
1835 }

1839  UNREACHABLE();
1840 }
1841 
1842 CompilationJob::Status WasmTurboshaftWrapperCompilationJob::ExecuteJobImpl(
1843  RuntimeCallStats* stats, LocalIsolate* local_isolate) {
1844  if (v8_flags.turbo_stats || v8_flags.turbo_stats_nvp) {
1845  DCHECK_NULL(pipeline_statistics_);
1846  pipeline_statistics_ = std::make_unique<TurbofanPipelineStatistics>(
1847  &info_, wasm::GetWasmEngine()->GetOrCreateTurboStatistics(),
1848  &zone_stats_);
1849  pipeline_statistics_->BeginPhaseKind("V8.WasmStubCodegen");
1850  }
1851  TraceWrapperCompilation(&info_, &turboshaft_data_);
1852  Linkage linkage(call_descriptor_);
1853 
1854  turboshaft_data_.set_pipeline_statistics(pipeline_statistics_.get());
1855  turboshaft_data_.SetIsWasmWrapper(sig_);
1856 
1857  AccountingAllocator allocator;
1858  turboshaft_data_.InitializeGraphComponent(nullptr);
1859  BuildWasmWrapper(&turboshaft_data_, &allocator, turboshaft_data_.graph(),
1860  sig_, wrapper_info_);
1861  CodeTracer* code_tracer = nullptr;
1862  if (info_.trace_turbo_graph()) {
1863  // NOTE: We must not call `GetCodeTracer` if tracing is not enabled,
1864  // because it may not yet be initialized then and doing so from the
1865  // background thread is not threadsafe.
1866  code_tracer = turboshaft_data_.GetCodeTracer();
1867  }
1868  Zone printing_zone(&allocator, ZONE_NAME);
1869  turboshaft::PrintTurboshaftGraph(&turboshaft_data_, &printing_zone,
1870  code_tracer, "Graph generation");
1871 
1872  turboshaft::Pipeline turboshaft_pipeline(&turboshaft_data_);
1873  // Skip the LoopUnrolling, WasmGCOptimize and WasmLowering phases for
1874  // wrappers.
1875  // TODO(14108): Do we need value numbering if wasm_opt is turned off?
1876  if (v8_flags.wasm_opt) {
1877  if (!turboshaft_pipeline.Run<turboshaft::WasmOptimizePhase>()) {
1878  return FAILED;
1879  }
1880  }
1881 #if DEBUG
1882  if (!v8_flags.wasm_opt) {
1883  // We still need to lower allocation operations even with optimizations
1884  // being turned off.
1885  if (!turboshaft_pipeline.Run<turboshaft::WasmDebugMemoryLoweringPhase>()) {
1886  return FAILED;
1887  }
1888  }
1889 #endif
1890 
1891  if (!Is64()) {
1892  if (!turboshaft_pipeline.Run<turboshaft::Int64LoweringPhase>()) {
1893  return FAILED;
1894  }
1895  }
1896 
1897  if (!turboshaft_pipeline.Run<turboshaft::WasmDeadCodeEliminationPhase>()) {
1898  return FAILED;
1899  }
1900 
1901  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.turboshaft_enable_debug_features)) {
1902  // This phase has to run very late to allow all previous phases to use
1903  // debug features.
1904  if (!turboshaft_pipeline.Run<turboshaft::DebugFeatureLoweringPhase>()) {
1905  return FAILED;
1906  }
1907  }
1908 
1909  turboshaft_pipeline.BeginPhaseKind("V8.InstructionSelection");
1910 
1911  const bool success = GenerateCodeFromTurboshaftGraph(
1912  &linkage, turboshaft_pipeline, &pipeline_);
1913  return success ? SUCCEEDED : FAILED;
1914 }

1916 CompilationJob::Status WasmTurboshaftWrapperCompilationJob::FinalizeJobImpl(
1917  Isolate* isolate) {
1918  return FinalizeWrapperCompilation(
1919  &turboshaft_data_, &info_, call_descriptor_, isolate,
1920  "WasmTurboshaftWrapperCompilationJob::FinalizeJobImpl");
1921 }

1925 void PipelineImpl::RunPrintAndVerify(const char* phase, bool untyped) {
1926  if (info()->trace_turbo_json() || info()->trace_turbo_graph()) {
1927  USE(Run<PrintGraphPhase>(phase));
1928  }
1929  if (v8_flags.turbo_verify) {
1930  USE(Run<VerifyGraphPhase>(untyped));
1931  }
1932 }
1933 
1934 bool PipelineImpl::InitializeHeapBroker() {
1935  TFPipelineData* data = data_;
1936 
1937  data->BeginPhaseKind("V8.TFBrokerInitAndSerialization");
1938 
1939  if (info()->trace_turbo_json() || info()->trace_turbo_graph()) {
1940  CodeTracer::StreamScope tracing_scope(data->GetCodeTracer());
1941  tracing_scope.stream()
1942  << "---------------------------------------------------\n"
1943  << "Begin compiling method " << info()->GetDebugName().get()
1944  << " using TurboFan" << std::endl;
1945  }
1946  if (info()->trace_turbo_json()) {
1947  TurboCfgFile tcf(isolate());
1948  tcf << AsC1VCompilation(info());
1949  }
1950  if (data->info()->has_bytecode_array()) {
1951  if (data->info()->bytecode_array()->SourcePositionTable()->DataSize() ==
1952  0) {
1953  data->source_positions()->Disable();
1954  }
1955  data->source_positions()->AddDecorator();
1956  }
1957  if (data->info()->trace_turbo_json()) {
1958  data->node_origins()->AddDecorator();
1959  }
1960 
1961  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(HeapBrokerInitializationPhase);
1962  data->broker()->StopSerializing();
1963  data->EndPhaseKind();
1964  return !info()->was_cancelled();
1965 }
1966 
1967 bool PipelineImpl::CreateGraph(Linkage* linkage) {
1968  DCHECK(!v8_flags.turbolev);
1969  TFPipelineData* data = this->data_;
1970  UnparkedScopeIfNeeded unparked_scope(data->broker());
1971 
1972  data->BeginPhaseKind("V8.TFGraphCreation");
1973 
1974  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(GraphBuilderPhase, linkage);
1975  RunPrintAndVerify(GraphBuilderPhase::phase_name(), true);
1976 
1977  // Perform function context specialization and inlining (if enabled).
1978  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(InliningPhase);
1979  RunPrintAndVerify(InliningPhase::phase_name(), true);
1980 
1981  // Determine the Typer operation flags.
1982  {
1983  SharedFunctionInfoRef shared_info =
1984  MakeRef(data->broker(), info()->shared_info());
1985  if (is_sloppy(shared_info.language_mode()) &&
1986  shared_info.IsUserJavaScript()) {
1987  // Sloppy mode functions always have an Object for this.
1988  data->AddTyperFlag(Typer::kThisIsReceiver);
1989  }
1990  if (IsClassConstructor(shared_info.kind())) {
1991  // Class constructors cannot be [[Call]]ed.
1992  data->AddTyperFlag(Typer::kNewTargetIsReceiver);
1993  }
1994  }
1995 
1996  data->EndPhaseKind();
1997 
1998  return !info()->was_cancelled();
1999 }
2000 
2001 bool PipelineImpl::OptimizeTurbofanGraph(Linkage* linkage) {
2002  DCHECK(!v8_flags.turbolev);
2003  TFPipelineData* data = this->data_;
2004 
2005  data->BeginPhaseKind("V8.TFLowering");
2006 
2007  // Trim the graph before typing to ensure all nodes are typed.
2008  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(EarlyGraphTrimmingPhase);
2009  RunPrintAndVerify(EarlyGraphTrimmingPhase::phase_name(), true);
2010 
2011  // Type the graph and keep the Typer running such that new nodes get
2012  // automatically typed when they are created.
2013  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(TyperPhase, data->CreateTyper());
2014  RunPrintAndVerify(TyperPhase::phase_name());
2015 
2016  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(TypedLoweringPhase);
2017  RunPrintAndVerify(TypedLoweringPhase::phase_name());
2018 
2019  if (data->info()->loop_peeling()) {
2020  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(LoopPeelingPhase);
2021  RunPrintAndVerify(LoopPeelingPhase::phase_name(), true);
2022  } else {
2023  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(LoopExitEliminationPhase);
2024  RunPrintAndVerify(LoopExitEliminationPhase::phase_name(), true);
2025  }
2026 
2027  if (v8_flags.turbo_load_elimination) {
2028  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(LoadEliminationPhase);
2029  RunPrintAndVerify(LoadEliminationPhase::phase_name());
2030  }
2031  data->DeleteTyper();
2032 
2033  if (v8_flags.turbo_escape) {
2034  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(EscapeAnalysisPhase);
2035  RunPrintAndVerify(EscapeAnalysisPhase::phase_name());
2036  }
2037 
2038  if (v8_flags.assert_types) {
2039  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(TypeAssertionsPhase);
2040  RunPrintAndVerify(TypeAssertionsPhase::phase_name());
2041  }
2042 
2043  // Perform simplified lowering. This has to run w/o the Typer decorator,
2044  // because we cannot compute meaningful types anyways, and the computed
2045  // types might even conflict with the representation/truncation logic.
2046  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(SimplifiedLoweringPhase, linkage);
2047  RunPrintAndVerify(SimplifiedLoweringPhase::phase_name(), true);
2048 
2049 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2050  if (data->has_js_wasm_calls()) {
2051  DCHECK(data->info()->inline_js_wasm_calls());
2052  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(JSWasmInliningPhase);
2053  RunPrintAndVerify(JSWasmInliningPhase::phase_name(), true);
2054 
2055  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(WasmTypingPhase, -1);
2056  RunPrintAndVerify(WasmTypingPhase::phase_name(), true);
2057 
2058  if (v8_flags.wasm_opt) {
2059  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(WasmGCOptimizationPhase, data->wasm_module_for_inlining(),
2060  data->jsgraph());
2061  RunPrintAndVerify(WasmGCOptimizationPhase::phase_name(), true);
2062  }
2063  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(JSWasmLoweringPhase);
2064  RunPrintAndVerify(JSWasmLoweringPhase::phase_name(), true);
2065 
2066  if (v8_flags.turbo_optimize_inlined_js_wasm_wrappers && v8_flags.wasm_opt) {
2067  wasm::WasmDetectedFeatures detected({wasm::WasmDetectedFeature::gc});
2068  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(WasmOptimizationPhase,
2069  MachineOperatorReducer::kSilenceSignallingNan, detected);
2070  RunPrintAndVerify(WasmOptimizationPhase::phase_name(), true);
2071  }
2072  }
2073 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2074 
2075  // From now on it is invalid to look at types on the nodes, because the
2076  // types on the nodes might not make sense after representation selection
2077  // due to the way we handle truncations; if we'd want to look at types
2078  // afterwards we'd essentially need to re-type (large portions of) the
2079  // graph.
2080 
2081  // In order to catch bugs related to type access after this point, we now
2082  // remove the types from the nodes (currently only in Debug builds).
2083 #ifdef DEBUG
2084  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(UntyperPhase);
2085  RunPrintAndVerify(UntyperPhase::phase_name(), true);
2086 #endif
2087 
2088  // Run generic lowering pass.
2089  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(GenericLoweringPhase);
2090  RunPrintAndVerify(GenericLoweringPhase::phase_name(), true);
2091 
2092  data->BeginPhaseKind("V8.TFBlockBuilding");
2093 
2094  data->InitializeFrameData(linkage->GetIncomingDescriptor());
2095 
2096  // Run early optimization pass.
2097  RUN_MAYBE_ABORT(EarlyOptimizationPhase);
2098  RunPrintAndVerify(EarlyOptimizationPhase::phase_name(), true);
2099 
2100  data->source_positions()->RemoveDecorator();
2101  if (data->info()->trace_turbo_json()) {
2102  data->node_origins()->RemoveDecorator();
2103  }
2104 
2105  if (!ComputeScheduledGraph()) return false;
2106 
2107  return !info()->was_cancelled();
2108 }

2110 namespace {
2111 
2112 int HashGraphForPGO(const turboshaft::Graph* graph) {
2113  size_t hash = 0;
2114  for (const turboshaft::Operation& op : graph->AllOperations()) {
2115  VisitOperation(op, [&hash, &graph](const auto& derived) {
2116  const auto op_hash =
2117  derived.hash_value(turboshaft::HashingStrategy::kMakeSnapshotStable);
2118  hash = turboshaft::fast_hash_combine(hash, op_hash);
2119  // Use for tracing while developing:
2120  constexpr bool kTraceHashing = false;
2121  if constexpr (kTraceHashing) {
2122  std::cout << "[" << std::setw(3) << graph->Index(derived)
2123  << "] Type: " << std::setw(30)
2124  << turboshaft::OpcodeName(
2125  turboshaft::operation_to_opcode_v<decltype(derived)>);
2126  std::cout << " + 0x" << std::setw(20) << std::left << std::hex
2127  << op_hash << " => 0x" << hash << std::dec << std::endl;
2128  }
2129  });
2130  }
2131  return Tagged<Smi>(IntToSmi(static_cast<int>(hash))).value();
2132 }
2133 
2134 // Compute a hash of the given graph, in a way that should provide the same
2135 // result in multiple runs of mksnapshot, meaning the hash cannot depend on any
2136 // external pointer values or uncompressed heap constants. This hash can be used
2137 // to reject profiling data if the builtin's current code doesn't match the
2138 // version that was profiled. Hash collisions are not catastrophic; in the worst
2139 // case, we just defer some blocks that ideally shouldn't be deferred. The
2140 // result value is in the valid Smi range.
2141 int HashGraphForPGO(const TFGraph* graph) {
2142  AccountingAllocator allocator;
2143  Zone local_zone(&allocator, ZONE_NAME);
2144 
2145  constexpr NodeId kUnassigned = static_cast<NodeId>(-1);
2146 
2147  constexpr uint8_t kUnvisited = 0;
2148  constexpr uint8_t kOnStack = 1;
2149  constexpr uint8_t kVisited = 2;
2150 
2151  // Do a depth-first post-order traversal of the graph. For every node, hash:
2152  //
2153  // - the node's traversal number
2154  // - the opcode
2155  // - the number of inputs
2156  // - each input node's traversal number
2157  //
2158  // What's a traversal number? We can't use node IDs because they're not stable
2159  // build-to-build, so we assign a new number for each node as it is visited.
2160 
2161  ZoneVector<uint8_t> state(graph->NodeCount(), kUnvisited, &local_zone);
2162  ZoneVector<NodeId> traversal_numbers(graph->NodeCount(), kUnassigned,
2163  &local_zone);
2164  ZoneStack<Node*> stack(&local_zone);
2165 
2166  NodeId visited_count = 0;
2167  size_t hash = 0;
2168 
2169  stack.push(graph->end());
2170  state[graph->end()->id()] = kOnStack;
2171  traversal_numbers[graph->end()->id()] = visited_count++;
2172  while (!stack.empty()) {
2173  Node* n = stack.top();
2174  bool pop = true;
2175  for (Node* const i : n->inputs()) {
2176  if (state[i->id()] == kUnvisited) {
2177  state[i->id()] = kOnStack;
2178  traversal_numbers[i->id()] = visited_count++;
2179  stack.push(i);
2180  pop = false;
2181  break;
2182  }
2183  }
2184  if (pop) {
2185  state[n->id()] = kVisited;
2186  stack.pop();
2187  hash = base::hash_combine(hash, traversal_numbers[n->id()], n->opcode(),
2188  n->InputCount());
2189  for (Node* const i : n->inputs()) {
2190  DCHECK(traversal_numbers[i->id()] != kUnassigned);
2191  hash = base::hash_combine(hash, traversal_numbers[i->id()]);
2192  }
2193  }
2194  }
2195  return Tagged<Smi>(IntToSmi(static_cast<int>(hash))).value();
2196 }
2197 
2198 template <typename Graph>
2199 int ComputeInitialGraphHash(Builtin builtin,
2200  const ProfileDataFromFile* profile_data,
2201  const Graph* graph) {
2202  int initial_graph_hash = 0;
2203  if (v8_flags.turbo_profiling || v8_flags.dump_builtins_hashes_to_file ||
2204  profile_data != nullptr) {
2205  initial_graph_hash = HashGraphForPGO(graph);
2206  if (v8_flags.dump_builtins_hashes_to_file) {
2207  std::ofstream out(v8_flags.dump_builtins_hashes_to_file,
2208  std::ios_base::app);
2209  out << "Builtin: " << Builtins::name(builtin) << ", hash: 0x" << std::hex
2210  << initial_graph_hash << std::endl;
2211  }
2212  }
2213  return initial_graph_hash;
2214 }
2215 
2216 const ProfileDataFromFile* ValidateProfileData(
2217  const ProfileDataFromFile* profile_data, int initial_graph_hash,
2218  const char* debug_name) {
2219  if (profile_data != nullptr && profile_data->hash() != initial_graph_hash) {
2220  if (v8_flags.reorder_builtins) {
2221  BuiltinsCallGraph::Get()->set_all_hash_matched(false);
2222  }
2223  if (v8_flags.abort_on_bad_builtin_profile_data ||
2224  v8_flags.warn_about_builtin_profile_data) {
2225  base::EmbeddedVector<char, 256> msg;
2226  SNPrintF(
2227  msg,
2228  "Rejected profile data for %s due to function change. "
2229  "Please use tools/builtins-pgo/generate.py to refresh it, you can "
2230  "also try adding `'checkout_pgo_profiles': True` to your .gclient "
2231  "file and run `gclient sync` to download the latest PGO profiles.",
2232  debug_name);
2233  if (v8_flags.abort_on_bad_builtin_profile_data) {
2234  // mksnapshot might fail here because of the following reasons:
2235  // * builtins were changed since the builtins profile generation,
2236  // * current build options affect builtins code and they don't match
2237  // the options used for building the profile (for example, it might
2238  // be because of gn argument 'dcheck_always_on=true').
2239  // To fix the issue one must either update the builtins PGO profiles
2240  // (see tools/builtins-pgo/generate.py) or disable builtins PGO by
2241  // setting gn argument v8_builtins_profiling_log_file="".
2242  // One might also need to update the tools/builtins-pgo/generate.py if
2243  // the set of default release arguments has changed.
2244  FATAL("%s", msg.begin());
2245  } else {
2246  PrintF("%s\n", msg.begin());
2247  }
2248  }
2249 #ifdef LOG_BUILTIN_BLOCK_COUNT
2250  if (v8_flags.turbo_log_builtins_count_input) {
2251  PrintF("The hash came from execution count file for %s was not match!\n",
2252  debug_name);
2253  }
2254 #endif
2255  return nullptr;
2256  }
2257  return profile_data;
2258 }

2310 PipelineCompilationJob::Status CodeAssemblerCompilationJob::PrepareJobImpl(
2311  Isolate* isolate) {
2312  {
2313  // Work around that the PersistentHandlesScope inside CompilationHandleScope
2314  // requires there to be at least one handle.
2315  HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
2316  DirectHandle<Object> dummy(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate->heap()).empty_string(),
2317  isolate);
2318  CompilationHandleScope compilation_scope(isolate, &compilation_info_);
2319  generator_(&code_assembler_state_);
2320  }
2321 
2322  node_origins_.emplace(raw_assembler()->ExportForOptimization());
2323 
2324  PipelineImpl* pipeline = EmplacePipeline(isolate);
2325  TFPipelineData* data = pipeline->data();
2326  PipelineJobScope pipeline_scope(data,
2327  isolate->counters()->runtime_call_stats());
2328  if (v8_flags.turbo_stats || v8_flags.turbo_stats_nvp) {
2329  pipeline_statistics_.reset(new TurbofanPipelineStatistics(
2330  &compilation_info_, isolate->GetTurboStatistics(), &zone_stats_));
2331  }
2332 
2333  const char* debug_name = code_assembler_state_.name_;
2334  if (compilation_info_.trace_turbo_json() ||
2335  compilation_info_.trace_turbo_graph()) {
2336  CodeTracer::StreamScope tracing_scope(data->GetCodeTracer());
2337  tracing_scope.stream()
2338  << "---------------------------------------------------\n"
2339  << "Begin compiling " << debug_name << " using TurboFan" << std::endl;
2340  if (compilation_info_.trace_turbo_json()) {
2341  TurboJsonFile json_of(&compilation_info_, std::ios_base::trunc);
2342  json_of << "{\"function\" : ";
2343  JsonPrintFunctionSource(json_of, -1, compilation_info_.GetDebugName(),
2344  DirectHandle<Script>(), isolate,
2345  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo>());
2346  json_of << ",\n\"phases\":[";
2347  }
2348  if (!pipeline->Run<PrintGraphPhase>("V8.TFMachineCode")) return FAILED;
2349  }
2350 
2351  // Validate pgo profile.
2352  initial_graph_hash_ = ComputeInitialGraphHash(compilation_info_.builtin(),
2353  profile_data_, data->graph());
2354  profile_data_ = ValidateProfileData(profile_data_, initial_graph_hash_,
2355  code_assembler_state_.name_);
2356  data->set_profile_data(profile_data_);
2357 
2358  return SUCCEEDED;
2359 }
2360 
2361 PipelineCompilationJob::Status CodeAssemblerCompilationJob::FinalizeJobImpl(
2362  Isolate* isolate) {
2363  RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kOptimizeFinalizePipelineJob);
2364 
2365  HandleScope scope(isolate);
2366  Handle<Code> code = FinalizeCode(isolate);
2367 
2368 #ifdef ENABLE_DISASSEMBLER
2369  if (v8_flags.trace_ignition_codegen &&
2370  code->kind() == CodeKind::BYTECODE_HANDLER) {
2371  StdoutStream os;
2372  code->Disassemble(code_assembler_state_.name_, os, isolate);
2373  os << std::flush;
2374  }
2375 #endif // ENABLE_DISASSEMBLER
2376 
2377  code_assembler_state_.code_generated_ = true;
2378  installer_(compilation_info_.builtin(), scope.CloseAndEscape(code));
2379 
2380  return SUCCEEDED;
2381 }

2419 PipelineCompilationJob::Status
2420 CodeAssemblerTurboshaftCompilationJob::ExecuteJobImpl(
2421  RuntimeCallStats* stats, LocalIsolate* local_isolate) {
2422  if (!pipeline_->pipeline.ComputeScheduledGraph()) return FAILED;
2423  DCHECK_NULL(pipeline_->data.frame());
2424  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(pipeline_->data.schedule());
2425 
2426  turboshaft::BuiltinPipeline turboshaft_pipeline(&turboshaft_data_.value());
2427  CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = raw_assembler()->call_descriptor();
2428  Linkage linkage(call_descriptor);
2429 
2430  CHECK(
2431  turboshaft_pipeline.CreateGraphFromTurbofan(&pipeline_->data, &linkage));
2432 
2433  turboshaft_pipeline.OptimizeBuiltin();
2434 
2435  CHECK_NULL(pipeline_->data.osr_helper_ptr());
2436  CHECK(turboshaft_pipeline.GenerateCode(
2437  &linkage, pipeline_->data.osr_helper_ptr(), jump_opt_.get(),
2438  profile_data_, initial_graph_hash_));
2439 
2440  return SUCCEEDED;
2441 }

2448  turboshaft::Tracing::Scope tracing_scope(pipeline_->data.info());
2449  return turboshaft_pipeline.FinalizeCode().ToHandleChecked();
2450 }

2524 MaybeHandle<Code> Pipeline::GenerateCodeForTurboshaftBuiltin(
2525  turboshaft::PipelineData* turboshaft_data, CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
2526  Builtin builtin, const char* debug_name,
2527  const ProfileDataFromFile* profile_data) {
2528  DCHECK_EQ(builtin, turboshaft_data->info()->builtin());
2529  Isolate* isolate = turboshaft_data->isolate();
2530 
2531 #if V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_TSA_BUILTINS
2532 // TODO(nicohartmann): Use during development and remove afterwards.
2533 #ifdef DEBUG
2534  std::cout << "=== Generating Builtin '" << debug_name
2535  << "' with Turboshaft ===" << std::endl;
2536 #endif
2537 
2538 #endif
2539 
2540  // Initialize JumpOptimizationInfo if required.
2541  JumpOptimizationInfo jump_opt;
2542  bool should_optimize_jumps =
2543  isolate->serializer_enabled() && v8_flags.turbo_rewrite_far_jumps &&
2544  !v8_flags.turbo_profiling && !v8_flags.dump_builtins_hashes_to_file;
2545  JumpOptimizationInfo* jump_optimization_info =
2546  should_optimize_jumps ? &jump_opt : nullptr;
2547 
2548  PipelineJobScope scope(turboshaft_data,
2549  isolate->counters()->runtime_call_stats());
2550  RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kOptimizeCode);
2551 
2552  std::unique_ptr<TurbofanPipelineStatistics> pipeline_statistics(
2553  CreatePipelineStatistics(Handle<Script>::null(), turboshaft_data->info(),
2554  isolate, turboshaft_data->zone_stats()));
2555 
2556  turboshaft::BuiltinPipeline turboshaft_pipeline(turboshaft_data);
2557  OptimizedCompilationInfo* info = turboshaft_data->info();
2558  if (info->trace_turbo_graph() || info->trace_turbo_json()) {
2559  turboshaft::ZoneWithName<turboshaft::kTempZoneName> print_zone(
2560  turboshaft_data->zone_stats(), turboshaft::kTempZoneName);
2561  std::vector<char> name_buffer(strlen("TSA: ") + strlen(debug_name) + 1);
2562  memcpy(name_buffer.data(), "TSA: ", 5);
2563  memcpy(name_buffer.data() + 5, debug_name, strlen(debug_name));
2564  turboshaft_pipeline.PrintGraph(print_zone, name_buffer.data());
2565  }
2566 
2567  // Validate pgo profile.
2568  const int initial_graph_hash =
2569  ComputeInitialGraphHash(builtin, profile_data, &turboshaft_data->graph());
2570  profile_data =
2571  ValidateProfileData(profile_data, initial_graph_hash, debug_name);
2572 
2573  turboshaft_pipeline.OptimizeBuiltin();
2574  Linkage linkage(call_descriptor);
2575  CHECK(turboshaft_pipeline.GenerateCode(&linkage, {}, jump_optimization_info,
2576  profile_data, initial_graph_hash));
2577  return turboshaft_pipeline.FinalizeCode();
2578 }

2584 wasm::WasmCompilationResult WrapperCompilationResult(
2585  CodeGenerator* code_generator, CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
2586  CodeKind kind) {
2587  wasm::WasmCompilationResult result;
2588  code_generator->masm()->GetCode(
2589  nullptr, &result.code_desc, code_generator->safepoint_table_builder(),
2590  static_cast<int>(code_generator->handler_table_offset()));
2591  result.instr_buffer = code_generator->masm()->ReleaseBuffer();
2592  result.source_positions = code_generator->GetSourcePositionTable();
2593  result.protected_instructions_data =
2594  code_generator->GetProtectedInstructionsData();
2595  result.frame_slot_count = code_generator->frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount();
2596  result.tagged_parameter_slots = call_descriptor->GetTaggedParameterSlots();
2597  result.result_tier = wasm::ExecutionTier::kTurbofan;
2598  if (kind == CodeKind::WASM_TO_JS_FUNCTION) {
2599  result.kind = wasm::WasmCompilationResult::kWasmToJsWrapper;
2600  }
2601  return result;
2602 }

2629  tracing_scope.stream()
2630  << "---------------------------------------------------\n"

2638 // static
2639 wasm::WasmCompilationResult Pipeline::GenerateCodeForWasmNativeStub(
2640  CallDescriptor* call_descriptor, MachineGraph* mcgraph, CodeKind kind,
2641  const char* debug_name, const AssemblerOptions& options,
2642  SourcePositionTable* source_positions) {
2643  TFGraph* graph = mcgraph->graph();
2644  OptimizedCompilationInfo info(base::CStrVector(debug_name), graph->zone(),
2645  kind);
2646  // Construct a pipeline for scheduling and code generation.
2647  wasm::WasmEngine* wasm_engine = wasm::GetWasmEngine();
2648  ZoneStats zone_stats(wasm_engine->allocator());
2649  NodeOriginTable* node_positions = graph->zone()->New<NodeOriginTable>(graph);
2650  TFPipelineData data(&zone_stats, wasm_engine, &info, mcgraph, nullptr,
2651  source_positions, node_positions, options);
2652  std::unique_ptr<TurbofanPipelineStatistics> pipeline_statistics;
2653  if (v8_flags.turbo_stats || v8_flags.turbo_stats_nvp) {
2654  pipeline_statistics.reset(new TurbofanPipelineStatistics(
2655  &info, wasm_engine->GetOrCreateTurboStatistics(), &zone_stats));
2656  pipeline_statistics->BeginPhaseKind("V8.WasmStubCodegen");
2657  }
2658  TraceWrapperCompilation("TurboFan", &info, &data);
2659 
2660  PipelineImpl pipeline(&data);
2661  pipeline.RunPrintAndVerify("V8.WasmNativeStubMachineCode", true);
2662 
2663  CHECK(pipeline.Run<MemoryOptimizationPhase>());
2664  pipeline.RunPrintAndVerify(MemoryOptimizationPhase::phase_name(), true);
2665 
2666  CHECK(pipeline.ComputeScheduledGraph());
2667 
2668  Linkage linkage(call_descriptor);
2669 
2670  turboshaft::PipelineData turboshaft_data(
2671  &zone_stats, turboshaft::TurboshaftPipelineKind::kWasm, nullptr, &info,
2672  options);
2673  turboshaft::Pipeline turboshaft_pipeline(&turboshaft_data);
2674 
2675  CHECK(turboshaft_pipeline.CreateGraphFromTurbofan(&data, &linkage));
2676  // We need to run simplification to normalize some patterns for instruction
2677  // selection (e.g. loads and stores).
2678  CHECK(turboshaft_pipeline.RunSimplificationAndNormalizationPhase());
2679 
2680  CHECK(GenerateCodeFromTurboshaftGraph(&linkage, turboshaft_pipeline,
2681  &pipeline, data.osr_helper_ptr()));
2682 
2683  auto result = WrapperCompilationResult(turboshaft_data.code_generator(),
2684  call_descriptor, kind);
2685  DCHECK(result.succeeded());
2686  CodeTracer* code_tracer = nullptr;
2687  if (info.trace_turbo_json() || info.trace_turbo_graph()) {
2688  code_tracer = data.GetCodeTracer();
2689  }
2690  TraceFinishWrapperCompilation(info, code_tracer, result,
2691  pipeline.code_generator());
2692  return result;
2693 }

2695 // static
2696 wasm::WasmCompilationResult
2697 Pipeline::GenerateCodeForWasmNativeStubFromTurboshaft(
2698  const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig, wasm::WrapperCompilationInfo wrapper_info,
2699  const char* debug_name, const AssemblerOptions& options,
2700  SourcePositionTable* source_positions) {
2701  wasm::WasmEngine* wasm_engine = wasm::GetWasmEngine();
2702  Zone zone(wasm_engine->allocator(), ZONE_NAME);
2703  WasmCallKind call_kind =
2704  wrapper_info.code_kind == CodeKind::WASM_TO_JS_FUNCTION
2705  ? WasmCallKind::kWasmImportWrapper
2706  : WasmCallKind::kWasmCapiFunction;
2707  CallDescriptor* call_descriptor =
2708  GetWasmCallDescriptor(&zone, sig, call_kind);
2709  if (!Is64()) {
2710  call_descriptor = GetI32WasmCallDescriptor(&zone, call_descriptor);
2711  }
2712  Linkage linkage(call_descriptor);
2713  OptimizedCompilationInfo info(base::CStrVector(debug_name), &zone,
2714  wrapper_info.code_kind);
2715  ZoneStats zone_stats(wasm_engine->allocator());
2716  TFPipelineData data(&zone_stats, &info, nullptr,
2717  wasm::GetWasmEngine()->allocator(), nullptr, nullptr,
2718  nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, options, nullptr);
2719  std::unique_ptr<TurbofanPipelineStatistics> pipeline_statistics;
2720  if (v8_flags.turbo_stats || v8_flags.turbo_stats_nvp) {
2721  pipeline_statistics.reset(new TurbofanPipelineStatistics(
2722  &info, wasm_engine->GetOrCreateTurboStatistics(), &zone_stats));
2723  pipeline_statistics->BeginPhaseKind("V8.WasmStubCodegen");
2724  }
2725  TraceWrapperCompilation("Turboshaft", &info, &data);
2726 
2727  PipelineImpl pipeline(&data);
2728 
2729  {
2730  turboshaft::PipelineData turboshaft_data(
2731  &zone_stats, turboshaft::TurboshaftPipelineKind::kWasm, nullptr, &info,
2732  options);
2733  turboshaft_data.SetIsWasmWrapper(sig);
2734  AccountingAllocator allocator;
2735  turboshaft_data.InitializeGraphComponent(source_positions);
2736  BuildWasmWrapper(&turboshaft_data, &allocator, turboshaft_data.graph(), sig,
2737  wrapper_info);
2738  CodeTracer* code_tracer = nullptr;
2739  if (info.trace_turbo_json() || info.trace_turbo_graph()) {
2740  // NOTE: We must not call `GetCodeTracer` if tracing is not enabled,
2741  // because it may not yet be initialized then and doing so from the
2742  // background thread is not threadsafe.
2743  code_tracer = data.GetCodeTracer();
2744  }
2745  Zone printing_zone(&allocator, ZONE_NAME);
2746  turboshaft::PrintTurboshaftGraph(&turboshaft_data, &printing_zone,
2747  code_tracer, "Graph generation");
2748 
2749  // Skip the LoopUnrolling, WasmGCOptimize and WasmLowering phases for
2750  // wrappers.
2751  // TODO(14108): Do we need value numbering if wasm_opt is turned off?
2752  turboshaft::Pipeline turboshaft_pipeline(&turboshaft_data);
2753  if (v8_flags.wasm_opt) {
2754  CHECK(turboshaft_pipeline.Run<turboshaft::WasmOptimizePhase>());
2755  }
2756 #if DEBUG
2757  if (!v8_flags.wasm_opt) {
2758  // We still need to lower allocation operations even with optimizations
2759  // being turned off.
2760  CHECK(
2761  turboshaft_pipeline.Run<turboshaft::WasmDebugMemoryLoweringPhase>());
2762  }
2763 #endif
2764 
2765  if (!Is64()) {
2766  CHECK(turboshaft_pipeline.Run<turboshaft::Int64LoweringPhase>());
2767  }
2768 
2769  CHECK(turboshaft_pipeline.Run<turboshaft::WasmDeadCodeEliminationPhase>());
2770 
2771  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.turboshaft_enable_debug_features)) {
2772  // This phase has to run very late to allow all previous phases to use
2773  // debug features.
2774  CHECK(turboshaft_pipeline.Run<turboshaft::DebugFeatureLoweringPhase>());
2775  }
2776 
2777  data.BeginPhaseKind("V8.InstructionSelection");
2778 
2779  const bool success = GenerateCodeFromTurboshaftGraph(
2780  &linkage, turboshaft_pipeline, &pipeline, data.osr_helper_ptr());
2781  CHECK(success);
2782 
2783  auto result =
2784  WrapperCompilationResult(turboshaft_data.code_generator(),
2785  call_descriptor, wrapper_info.code_kind);
2786  DCHECK(result.succeeded());
2787 
2788  TraceFinishWrapperCompilation(info, code_tracer, result,
2789  turboshaft_data.code_generator());
2790  return result;
2791  }
2792 }

2794 namespace {
2795 
2796 base::OwnedVector<uint8_t> SerializeInliningPositions(
2797  const ZoneVector<WasmInliningPosition>& positions) {
2798  const size_t entry_size = sizeof positions[0].inlinee_func_index +
2799  sizeof positions[0].was_tail_call +
2800  sizeof positions[0].caller_pos;
2801  auto result = base::OwnedVector<uint8_t>::New(positions.size() * entry_size);
2802  uint8_t* iter = result.begin();
2803  for (const auto& [func_index, was_tail_call, caller_pos] : positions) {
2804  size_t index_size = sizeof func_index;
2805  std::memcpy(iter, &func_index, index_size);
2806  iter += index_size;
2807  size_t was_tail_call_size = sizeof was_tail_call;
2808  std::memcpy(iter, &was_tail_call, was_tail_call_size);
2809  iter += was_tail_call_size;
2810  size_t pos_size = sizeof caller_pos;
2811  std::memcpy(iter, &caller_pos, pos_size);
2812  iter += pos_size;
2813  }
2814  DCHECK_EQ(iter, result.end());
2815  return result;
2816 }

2921 
2922  data.BeginPhaseKind("V8.WasmOptimization");
2923  turboshaft::Pipeline turboshaft_pipeline(&turboshaft_data);
2924 
2925 #if defined(V8_ENABLE_WASM_SIMD256_REVEC) && defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_X64)

2939  }
2940  }
2941 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WASM_SIMD256_REVEC
2942 
2943  const bool uses_wasm_gc_features =
2944  detected->has_gc() || detected->has_typed_funcref() ||
2945  detected->has_stringref() || detected->has_imported_strings() ||
2946  detected->has_imported_strings_utf8();

2986  }
2987 #endif
2988 
2989  if (mcgraph->machine()->Is32()) {
2990  CHECK(turboshaft_pipeline.Run<turboshaft::Int64LoweringPhase>());
2991  }

2999  }
3000 
3001  data.BeginPhaseKind("V8.InstructionSelection");
3002 
3003  // Instruction selection for JavaScript may fail, but for Wasm we should
3004  // always succeed (e.g., by enforcing limits in earlier phases).
3005  CHECK(GenerateCodeFromTurboshaftGraph(&linkage, turboshaft_pipeline,
3006  &pipeline, data.osr_helper_ptr()));
3007 
3008  CodeGenerator* code_generator = turboshaft_data.code_generator();
3009 
3010  wasm::WasmCompilationResult result;
3011  code_generator->masm()->GetCode(
3012  nullptr, &result.code_desc, code_generator->safepoint_table_builder(),
3013  static_cast<int>(code_generator->handler_table_offset()));
3014

3016  result.frame_slot_count = code_generator->frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount();
3017  result.tagged_parameter_slots = call_descriptor->GetTaggedParameterSlots();
3018  result.source_positions = code_generator->GetSourcePositionTable();
3019  result.inlining_positions = SerializeInliningPositions(inlining_positions);

3021  code_generator->GetProtectedInstructionsData();
3022  result.deopt_data = code_generator->GenerateWasmDeoptimizationData();
3023  result.result_tier = wasm::ExecutionTier::kTurbofan;
3024

3052  << "Finished compiling method " << data.info()->GetDebugName().get()
3053  << " using Turboshaft" << std::endl;
3054  }

3074  static_cast<int>(std::min(size_t{kMaxInt}, zone_bytes)));

3077  // Add a "0 deopts" sample for the first tier-up of a function that contains

3094 
3095  DCHECK(result.succeeded());
3096  return result;
3097 }
